##Quanzhou Quarantine Hotel collapse: COLUMNS DEFORMED MINUTES BEFORE COLLAPSE, hotel owner under police control | deep focus

MICRO-SIGNAL BQSHENYIDU

Beijing Youth Daily reports from the official public number

Reporter / Cao Huiru, Li Jianan, Tong Xiaoyu and Li Dong intern reporter / Zhou Manqing

Editor / Edward Shek, Jianhua Song

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A 17-story building collapsed in Quanzhou

March 7,19:15, a building in the Licheng district of Quanzhou City collapsed, a total of 71 people trapped at the scene of the accident (excluding the 9 self-rescue escape) . As of 1214 hours on 8 March, 44 people had been rescued from the scene (including 4 dead, 1 in critical condition and 4 seriously injured) 

The building is located at 1688 South Ring Road, a total of seven floors, 11 companies registered at this address, the building is the first floor of the hotel lobby Xinjia, car sales shops and other shops, 2,3 floors of the company moved in, operating catering, foot bath center business, etc. , rooms on the 4th floor and above are hotel rooms.

The Xinjia Express Hotel in the building opened in June 2018 and has about 66 rooms of various types. After the outbreak, Licheng district of Quanzhou City was transformed into a district-level medical observation point to isolate people arriving from key epidemic areas in Quanzhou.

Quanzhou Licheng District Housing Bureau director confirmed to the media that the hotel on the first floor before the Spring Festival began to transform. At 7 p.m. on March 7, the owner of the hotel received a phone call from the construction workers at the scene that a column in the ground floor of the building where the work was being carried out had been deformed. Three or four minutes later, the whole building collapsed. The collapse of the building is due to decoration or the original structural problems, there is a need for further identification.

According to Xinhua, the hotel building collapse was caused by renovation work and the owner, surnamed Yang, has been investigated by the Public Security Bureau.

With the collapse of the original Xinjia Hotel, after the outbreak, the hotel became an isolation point

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"In two or three seconds, the whole building will collapse. "

Li Li Li's home in the four seasons Kangcheng Phase I, next to the Xinjia Hotel, about 7:10 pm on the 7th, Li Li Li originally intended to park the car in front of the hotel on an empty lot, suddenly heard the "crackling" sound of broken glass on the ground.

She thought someone had quarreled and threw bottles down the stairs. Fearing that her car would be damaged, Li Li parked her car in front of a gas station 30 meters away from the hotel. Later, she went to the gas station bathroom, and when she came out, she saw three or four men in police uniforms in front of the hotel. Li Li went up to tell the other party, someone threw bottles upstairs, the other party ignored her, went straight to the hotel.

At this time, Li Li saw two waiters in front of the hotel to clean up the broken glass. A man parked his car outside the door and hurried into the hotel lobby. Li Li want to remind each other to pay attention to the safety of the car, "boom" came, she ran away as fast as she could, it seemed only two or three seconds, the whole building collapsed, a large smoke.

"It was like an explosion, like an earthquake. I thought the oil depot had exploded. " Jiang Tian was waiting at a gas station next to the hotel when the accident happened. The gas station was small, with only two gas stations and four cars in line.

The noise was followed by a deluge of dust. "The dust was so big that nothing could be seen, " Jiang said. The gas station employee returned the gun and shouted "no more gas" . The employee and the owner of the car ran out as fast as they could.

It wasn't until four or five minutes later, when the dust cleared, that Jiang Tian was able to see clearly through the bright street lights.

The collapse of the gas station is a straight line about 30 meters away from the Xin Jia Hotel, hotel collapse, a large number of glass fragments, bricks smashed in the open space in front of the gas station.

According to Jiang, this is Quanzhou's used-car market, with many car sales and repair shops nearby. "We went over and saw that the house had collapsed, as if it was made of steel. It fell in one direction and hit several cars on the sidewalk in front of the hotel. Some of the lights were still on. " Jiang Tian saw five or six cars hit, a small white car with a rock falling on its head and its back sticking up.

The rain was still falling, and after the dust dissipated, the debris was overcast and there was no sound of rescue. A few minutes later, the Fire Department, the Public Security Bureau, the traffic police, and the 120 ambulance came to the scene one after another.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Firefighters are on the scene

A few minutes before the collapse, workers reported column deformation

The Xinjia hotel in Licheng District, Quanzhou was incorporated on March 28,2018, with Yang Jinqiang as the legal representative, according to business information.

On August 19,2019, the hotel underwent a change of premises. "6th floor" , no. 1688, Nanhuan Road, Shangcun community, Changtai Street, Licheng district, Quanzhou City, Fujian Province, was replaced by "floor 1 hall, floors 4 to 6" .

According to the hotel booking platform, Xinjia hotel, Quanzhou, opened in 2018 after renovation. It is located at 1688 Nanhuan road, Licheng district, Quanzhou City, next to the first phase of Zhongjun Siji Kangcheng. There are 80 rooms on the 4th to 7th floors. A number of interviewees confirmed that the building has enterprises in 2 floors, 3 floors mainly engaged in catering, the first floor in addition to Xinjia hotel lobby, the other side of the car sales, beauty shops.

In the less than two years since the establishment of the hotel, as a result of the failure to register for accommodation has been three administrative penalties, a cumulative fine of nearly, Yuan. The most recent punishment was on December 4,2019, when Xinjia hotel was ordered by the Licheng branch of the Quanzhou Public Security Bureau to rectify the situation immediately and fined 3,000 yuan for failing to register as required, according to the administrative punishment letter.

On July 17,2019, he was listed in the business exception list of the Licheng branch of the Quanzhou Administration for Industry and Commerce for failing to submit the annual report as required by the "measures on annual reports of individual industrial and commercial households" .

According to Zhang Yun, a tenant of the building, the building has seven floors and is made of steel. Since 2013, the downstairs shops have been rented out and the tenants have carried out their first renovation on their own. Starting in 2015, Zhang rented the first and second floor shops to use as 4s shop exhibition hall, Operating Car Sales Company.

Zhang Yun, the entire floor of the exhibition hall for the original State, a total of more than 800 square meters. Later, the middle is separated by a partition wall, the two businesses operate separately, sharing a parking lot. The outer side of the exhibition hall is 8 meters high, and the inner side is a two-storey office area.

At one point, she told me, the building had been vacant from three to six floors until 2017, when the landlord partnered with someone to turn it into a hotel. Zhang remembers that the glass on the outside of the building had broken several times in a year. The landlord replaced the glass on the outside of the building twice, and the tenants also replaced the glass in the office area.

A person familiar with the matter said in an interview with the media, "until 2017, each floor of the building will have an open lobby. The Xinjia hotel will open upstairs, and in 2017, cement and brick will be brought in, and the spacious lobby will be walled off into small rooms, and the hotel will open in 2018. ".

The building was built in 2013 and converted into a Xinjia Hotel in 2018, Zhang Yi, director of the Licheng District Housing Bureau of Quanzhou City, told the media on March 8. There are six on the ground floor of the building, two of which were originally supermarkets. Before the Spring Festival this year, the owner of the house will rent the first floor of the supermarket to take back to refit. At 7 p.m. on 7 March, the owner received a phone call from the construction workers at the site that a column in the ground floor of the building where the work was being carried out had been deformed. Three or four minutes later, the whole building collapsed.

Zhang Yi said that the building collapsed because of decoration or the original structure of the problem, still need to further identify.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Rescue workers rescued a buried crowd, rescue workers during the process of wearing a mask

Forty-four people have been rescued, four of them dead

Staff of the new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters in Licheng district, Quanzhou, told Shen once that the Xinjia hotel where the accident occurred was a local health observation point for the new crown pneumonia, mainly used for centralized quarantine observation from Hubei, Wenzhou and other key epidemic areas to personnel, quarantine personnel is not suspected cases, the area every day unified arrangement of health workers into the hotel.

On February 25, the Chen Zhen family of four and their sister, sister, son, brother-in-law, and seven others returned to Quanzhou from their hometown of Shishou, Hubei Province. The Chen Zhen family was placed under quarantine in a hotel in Fengze District, where they live by their community, and the three of them are staying at the Licheng District, Quanzhou Hotel.

After returning to Quanzhou from Hubei Province, Chen Zhen said, a few people checked into the hotel with simple toiletries because they were not allowed to enter the neighborhood. Because they had few relatives in the area, no one delivered food, so they had to order takeout after being quarantined in the hotel.

Only two days before the 14-day quarantine, at 8 p.m. on March 7, Chen Zhen received a phone call from her brother-in-law saying, "Oh no, the Xinjia hotel has collapsed. ". Chen Zhen panicked. She switched phones with her sisters, but no one answered.

Until 11 pm, Chen Zhen received a phone call from her brother-in-law, that 16-year-old nephew was rescued, the children's uncle and Mother did not know the situation, "please bless" , she kept repeating.

Two hours later, when news of their safe rescue reached Chen Zhen, he was relieved. "My brother-in-law spoke to them on the phone. He was a little weak and scared, but they were only slightly injured. ".

A man who survived the accident told the media that he had just taken a bath when he suddenly jumped into the air, the lights went out, everything was dark and his feet were covered with blood. "there was a couple on the left with their legs pinned down, and there was a man on the right who was badly pinned down. When the firemen came to the rescue, I said Save the People next to me first. I could still stand on my own feet. "

At 1:02 a.m. on March 8, Chinese firefighters pulled a baby from the rubble and blindfolded him with a mask, according to a statement posted on the official Weibo Account of the Chinese fire service. The parents were also rescued.

According to Chinese fire sources, the command center of Quanzhou's fire and rescue detachment immediately dispatched seven squadrons and more than 200 officers and men to the scene to deal with the collapse. The Fire Department also sent seven other rescue dogs across the region to reinforce. As of 1214 hours on 8 March, 44 people had been rescued from the scene (including 4 dead, 1 in critical condition and 4 seriously injured) .

To protect the privacy of the interviewees, the interviewees in this article are all pseudonyms
